</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB44B5AEE05FFC5FD4AFD3BFEB9566F" author="FRYER J. &amp; HYLMO B." pageId="12" pageNumber="151" refId="ref4629" refString="FRYER J. &amp; HYLMO B. 2009. - Cotoneasters: A Comprehensive Guide to Shrubs for Flowers, Fruit, and Foliage. Timber press, Portland, London, 344 p." type="book" year="2009">Fryer &amp; Hylmö 2009</bibRefCitation>
). As noted above, 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE05FFC5FE06FCDBFDFB566F" box="[481,593,790,816]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE05FFC5FE06FCDBFDFB566F" box="[481,593,790,816]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">C. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE05FFC5FD6FFCDBFCAD566F" box="[648,775,790,816]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellipticus">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE05FFC5FD6FFCDBFCAD566F" box="[648,775,790,816]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">C. ellipticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are closest relatives. Other than morphological differences, these species are geographically distinct. So, 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE05FFC5FDB5FC9BFD165630" box="[594,700,854,880]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE05FFC5FDB5FC9BFD165630" box="[594,700,854,880]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">C. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in west of 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE05FFC5FF14FCBBFE8956CF" box="[243,291,886,912]" name="Iran" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">Iran</collectingCountry>
, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE05FFC5FE8AFCBBFE4056D0" box="[365,490,885,912]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellipticus">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE05FFC5FE8AFCBBFE4056D0" box="[365,490,885,912]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">C. ellipticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the northeast of 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE05FFC5FF64FC5BFF1E56EF" box="[131,180,918,944]" name="Iran" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Consequently, the morphological differences and the discontinuous distribution provide sufficient evidence for treating 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE05FFC5FF06FC18FEF456B0" box="[225,350,981,1007]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ellipticus">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE05FFC5FF06FC18FEF456B0" box="[225,350,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">C. ellipticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE05FFC5FE74FC18FDA956B0" box="[403,515,981,1007]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE05FFC5FE74FC18FDA956B0" box="[403,515,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">C. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as separate species. The geographical distribution of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE05FFC5FE0DFC38FDF15150" box="[490,603,1013,1039]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="12" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE05FFC5FE0DFC38FDF15150" box="[490,603,1013,1039]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">C. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE05FFC5FD9DFC38FCA95150" box="[634,771,1013,1039]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE05FFC5FF63FBD8FEAC5170" box="[132,262,1045,1071]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
, Azerbaijan, 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE05FFC5FE79FBD8FDB85170" box="[414,530,1045,1071]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE05FFC5FDC6FBD8FDCA5170" box="[545,608,1045,1071]" name="India" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">India</collectingCountry>
, northwestern Himalaya (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB44B5AEE05FFC5FEE4FBF8FE2B5110" author="RIEDL H." box="[259,385,1077,1103]" pageId="12" pageNumber="151" pagination="13 - 26" refId="ref5495" refString="RIEDL H. 1969. - Cotoneaster Medik., in RECHINGER K. H. (ed.), Flora Iranica. Akademische Druck und Verlagsanstalt, Graz 66: 13 - 26." type="journal article" year="1969">Riedl 1969</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB44B5AEE05FFC5FE74FBF8FDE85110" author="POJARKOVA A. I." box="[403,578,1077,1103]" pageId="12" pageNumber="151" pagination="259 - 274" refId="ref5207" refString="POJARKOVA A. I. 1971. - Cotoneaster Medik., in KOMAROV V. L. (ed.), Flora of USSR. Keter press, Jerusalem 9: 259 - 274." type="journal article" year="1971">Pojarkova 1971</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB44B5AEE05FFC5FDB3FBF8FF175130" author="FRYER J. &amp; HYLMO B." pageId="12" pageNumber="151" refId="ref4629" refString="FRYER J. &amp; HYLMO B. 2009. - Cotoneasters: A Comprehensive Guide to Shrubs for Flowers, Fruit, and Foliage. Timber press, Portland, London, 344 p." type="book" year="2009">Fryer &amp; Hylmö 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and west of 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE05FFC5FEB1FB98FE2D5130" box="[342,391,1109,1135]" name="Iran" pageId="12" pageNumber="151">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF5A6623EE05FFC5FCCAFCAEFC7556FE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6573129" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6573129" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6573129/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="151" startId="12.[813,824,867,884]" targetBox="[906,1362,215,823]" targetPageId="12">
